**CADIA Project - Adobe Experience Manager (AEM) Services**
================================================================

**Solicitation Number:**
2023-00967

**Publication Date:**
2023-01-23

**Tender Closing Date:**
2023-03-06T14:00:00

**Contracting Entity:**
Canadian Food Inspection Agency
1400 Merivale Road, Ottawa, Ontario K1A 0Y9, Canada

**Project Overview:**
The Canadian Food Inspection Agency (CFIA) seeks to procure Adobe Experience Manager (AEM) services to support the delivery of digital services. The project will leverage existing capabilities inherent to CFIA's infrastructure and not rebuild functionality that already exists.

**Scope of Work:**

* One (1) x AEM Platform (Level 3) - Applications/Software Architect
* One (1) x AEM Platform (Level 3) - Programmer/Analyst

**Requirements:**

* Demonstrate qualification as an Indigenous Business as defined under the Procurement Strategy for Indigenous Business (PSIB)
* Comply with all requirements of PSIB
* Hold a valid TBIPS Supply Arrangement under Tier 1 for services in the National Capital Region
* Capabilities: Level 3 Applications/Software Architect and One (1) Level 3 Programmer/Analyst

**Notice Type:**
Request for Proposal

**Procurement Method:**
Competitive - Selective Tendering

**Trade Agreements:**
This procurement is open to suppliers who are eligible under the following trade agreements:
* Canada-Peru Free Trade Agreement (CPFTA)
* Canada-Colombia Free Trade Agreement
* Canada-Korea Free Trade Agreement (CKFTA)
* Canada-Chile Free Trade Agreement (CCFTA)
* Canada-Panama Free Trade Agreement
* Canada-European Union Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement (CETA)
* World Trade Organization Agreement on Government Procurement (WTO GPA)
* Canadian Free Trade Agreement (CFTA)

**Attachments:**
The notice document and solicitation package are available for download from the Canada Buys website.

**Contact Information:**

* Alexander Lisowski, Contact Person
* E-mail: [alexander.lisowski@inspection.gc.ca](mailto:alexander.lisowski@inspection.gc.ca)

**Documents:**
The tender description, requirements, and other relevant documents are available for download from the Canada Buys website.
